## Credibility Bank

*The proof that Evan has done the work — vetted for shareability. This brand operates primarily from the Interest Bank (documenting the journey) with a meaningful Credibility Bank underneath.*

**Bank type (per workshop framework):** Hybrid — Interest Bank primary (the journey is the content), Credibility Bank secondary (real wins back it up). The Interest Bank eventually becomes the Credibility Bank, but only through honesty. Never fake expertise. The wins below are real and shareable; they prove Evan is not a hobbyist, even though the biggest wins haven't happened yet.

### Wins (Green — Share Freely)

**Broadcast Alpha — March 3, 2026** — First live stream. 8 peak viewers on a channel told almost nobody about. No overlay, no polish — just showed up. Ran an 11-hour 39-minute radio broadcast (Holdt animation + Carson's lo-fi loop) without a single drop before going live. Built the animation loop from 480 raw PNGs, the countdown timer, and the patron roll typewriter overlay in the 48 hours before launch — all functional on day one. The tech stack worked. The stream happened. This is now a shareable credential: he shipped.

**Second Stream — March 4, 2026** — Showed up the next day on no sleep. Encountered two new technical issues (YouTube "made for kids" setting reset, chat disabled) and adapted in real time — restarted the stream, applied the checklist, kept going. The freeze is smaller. The stride moments are longer. The muscle is developing. He is still going.

**HTML/OBS technical capability (unlocked Mar 3–4)** — Through Claude pair-programming, Evan learned to build sophisticated OBS Browser Source overlays in HTML/CSS/JS. Built the countdown timer and patron roll typewriter from scratch. This is now a real production capability — not a one-off. The combination of Evan's technical fluency, Stream Deck automation, and HTML overlay building means OIS can do things in OBS that most creator brands hire agencies to approximate. This is a compounding advantage that will show up in every stream going forward.

**Kinfire Chronicles: Night's Fall** — Wrote quests for this tabletop RPG. Kickstarted, shipped to acclaim. Characters he created remain in the game after multiple expansions. This is his only public creative credit to date and it is fully shareable.

**Literary agent for The Keeper** — Brendan Deneen, former senior editor at Tor and President of Literary & IP Development at Assemble, offered representation after meeting in person in New York, December 2019. The Keeper was queried widely and received real attention before being retired on Evan's own terms.

**CAA Coverage — CONSIDER** — The Keeper received a CONSIDER rating from CAA coverage during the query campaign. Shareably impressive.

**The Keeper retired on his own terms** — He didn't get passed on by every publisher and quit. He read the feedback, did a paid editorial assessment, sat with it, and made the call himself. He wrote the retirement letter in May 2023. That's ownership of the narrative, not defeat.

**The Marathon Screenplay** — Co-written with Otis Blum. Currently out to directors through WME-connected manager John Burnham. An earlier pass attracted producers. It is a real screenplay that has made it into real rooms.

**The ONCE Mythology** — Seven original creation myths forming the complete cosmology of a fantasy world. Not worldbuilding notes. A moral philosophy built from scratch, with answers to the questions every civilization must answer. Being written in 2025–2026 in Analog, a year-long workshop led by Ravi Gupta. 6/7 outlines complete as of Mar 4. Target completion: Sep 9, 2026.

**18 years of almost daily writing** — The most unimpeachable credential. Every publisher praised the writing. Every rejection of The Keeper acknowledged real craft. The consistency is the proof.

### Scars (Green — The Brand Runs on These)

**The Rejection Ledger** — 7 film passes, 12+ agent passes, 10+ publisher passes. Tor, FSG, Harper, Bloomsbury, Del Rey, Viking, Sourcebooks. The CEO of Penguin Random House replied personally. Every major publisher on earth saw The Keeper. None bought it. And he kept going. The ledger is not a wound. It is a record. It belongs in the content.

**The rebrand from The Keeper** — He spent years on a book that didn't find a home. Then he retired it. Then he started something bigger. This is not failure. This is evolution visible in real time.

**The $10k Outside Inn investment before the brand was clear** — Built an atmosphere layer before building the creator brand it was meant to serve. The lesson is documented: validate before building. The reframe: the Outside Inn wasn't a wrong turn. It was the community layer before the creator brand existed to anchor it. It found its right place. The investment wasn't wasted; it was early.

**The first stream freeze** — 8 months of preparation, zero sleep, and the camera turned on and Evan froze. The only direction from here is up.

**The second stream restart** — Went live and realized YouTube had reset to "made for kids" — chat was locked, waiting room viewers bounced when the stream restarted. Adapted, restarted, kept going. The checklist now exists. This won't happen again.

