## The Outside Inn — Its Role in the Brand

**E.I. Werner is who you are. The Outside Inn is where your people go.**

Someone finds you through the work — a stream, a video, a clip. That's E.I. Werner. If they care enough to go deeper, they end up inside The Outside Inn — the Discord, the membership, the community. The inn is the place that exists because of the work. You can't have the inn without the writer who built it. One world. Two sides of the same door.

**The Outside Inn is the community of E.I. Werner.**

Not a second brand. Not a competing presence. The inside of the same world.

The relationship is clean: E.I. Werner is the creator — the work, the streams, the public face, the name on the door. The Outside Inn is what's behind it. The Discord, the membership tiers, the ambient broadcast, the second channel for true insiders. The room you end up in when you care enough to cross the threshold.

This distinction matters because the community needs a name, and "the E.I. Werner community" is a description, not a place. The Outside Inn is a place. It has history — it was the name of Evan's streaming presence in 2020–2021, which means the years of iteration weren't a wrong turn. The Outside Inn found its right relationship to the work. It belongs inside the E.I. Werner world, not parallel to it. The back-and-forth between Outside Inn as a brand and E.I. Werner as the focus wasn't confusion — it was the work of figuring out the right relationship between them. That work is done.

**What The Outside Inn is:**

**The Discord** — The community home. The open lobby for everyone. Tier-gated channels unlock for Innsiders and Innkeeps via Fourthwall integration.

**The warmup/cooldown atmosphere** — The 70:07 bookend that opens and closes every live stream. Holdt animation + Carson's music + patron roll. The inn as a felt experience before and after the work.

**The second YouTube channel** — A lower-stakes space for unscheduled streams, testing, tech runs, and the ambient broadcast. The channel that is simply *on* when it wants to be — Holdt animation, Carson's music, the inn as a place that exists even when Evan isn't actively streaming. Not a content channel. A place. People who find it are self-selecting as the most invested audience. Not formally launched yet — evaluate in Athens.

**The membership structure** — Innsider and Innkeep. The tiers describe what someone is in relation to the place, not just the work. You're not filing a credential. You pulled up a stool.

**What The Outside Inn is not:**

It is not a gaming channel. It is not a brand for a different audience. It is not the casual or secondary version of something more serious. The register inside the inn is warmer and looser, but the people are the same people — they just went deeper.

**The ambient broadcast:** The Outside Inn YouTube channel is the natural home for an ambient radio presence — Holdt animation, Carson's music, a place that hums along whether anyone is watching. The VPS infrastructure stays available for this purpose. This is not a 24/7 broadcast obligation — it is an atmosphere layer that can be turned on when it adds to the world. Not scheduled. Not required. Evaluate in Athens.

**The 70:07 Bookend:** The Outside Inn warmup/cooldown bookends every live stream — Holdt animation + Carson's music + patron roll, all running locally in OBS. No 24/7 radio. The bookend is the core atmosphere layer. It is live. It is enough.

**Font logic for warmup/cooldown scenes (updated Mar 4):**
- **Alagard** — pixel aesthetic, used in the warmup/cooldown patron roll. Matches Holdt/Marwan's art style.
- **Sprat** — clean, editorial, black and white. Used during live writing scenes. More on brand for the writing context, easier to read, signals a tonal shift from atmosphere to work.

The font change between scenes is a small but intentional signal: the warmup is the inn, the writing stream is the desk. Different registers of the same place.

**Discord:** The community Discord is called The Outside Inn. The open Discord is the lobby. Tier-gated channels unlock for Innsiders and Innkeeps via Fourthwall integration.

**Entity note:** Outside Inn Studios, LLC is the legal entity that operates everything. EIN 39-3932425. NY DOS ID 7690233. Formed August 20, 2025. Evan Werner, 100% member-managed.

