## Content Strategy

### The Cadence

**3 sessions per week: writing → gaming in each session.**

Each stream opens with writing — the ONCE mythology, live in Notion, with a defined goal for the session. Then transitions into gaming with community as the decompression and debrief. Writing is the main event. Gaming is the exhale. The 70:07 Outside Inn warmup opens every stream. The 70:07 cooldown closes it.

### The Growth Funnel — Three Layers

Growth is sequenced, not simultaneous. These layers build on each other. Do not skip ahead.

**Layer 1 — Deputize the homies.** The founding Innkeeps are not just members — they are co-owners of the culture. Give them their badges. Give them roles in Discord. Make them feel like the room is theirs, because it is. They recruit because they are proud of the place, not because they were asked. This layer is active now and never stops.

**Layer 2 — Warm network.** 700 IG followers, Facebook, LinkedIn, people in game. These people already like Evan. They just don't know this exists yet. One honest personal post or text converts at a far higher rate than any cold outreach. LinkedIn is underrated here specifically — a PM background, building something unusual, deploying to Athens is a story people share. The Athens launch Wednesday is the activation moment for this layer.

**Layer 3 — Vertical clips.** The scale lever. The skill being built toward. Once it works, it compounds. This is how new people find the room when they weren't already connected to Evan. The clip machine turns streams into discovery. Streams have to be worth clipping first — Athens is where that develops.

**The constraint:** Layers 1 and 2 are retention and warmth. Layer 3 is reach. You cannot retain people who never arrived. Do not invest heavily in Layer 3 until the stream itself is worth clipping consistently.

### Wednesday Athens Mini-Launch Goals (March 11, 2026)

The Wednesday stream from Athens is the first stream with real outreach — personal texts to extended network beyond the gaming community. These are the concrete targets:

- **1 person buys something** from the store
- **1 person becomes an Innsider** (paid or free)
- **1 person becomes an Innkeep** (paid or free founding member)
- **1 vertical clip** posted to E.I. Werner social accounts

These are not pressure targets. They are direction targets — they tell you what Wednesday needs to have in place to be possible. A store with one product, memberships live, patron roll running with founding Innkeep names.

### Monthly public update videos — ungated.

Straight look at how the month went, what moved, what didn't. These are the pieces most likely to bring new people in via recommendation. First one goes out April 7, 2026. Then the 7th of every month.

### The 75/20/5 Content Mix

**75% — Deep content.** ONCE mythology breakdowns, worldbuilding process, writing philosophy, the rejection ledger lived out loud, craft notes.

**20% — Niche-wide content.** Broadly relevant to fantasy lovers, gamers, and writers. Reaches new people adjacent to the offer.

**5% — Personal content (woven in, not standalone).** Gaming references, music taste, the nerdy obsessions, the human layer. *(Human layer inventory still needed — see Open Questions.)*

### The Content Success Formula

**Painful Problem + Unique Solution × Contextual Credibility × Proven Wrapper = Content That Converts**

Contextual credibility is more powerful than general credibility. Lead with the specific.

### Ideation Engine

Every painful problem from The Three Audiences section is a stream, a video, a conversation, a piece of content. Cross-reference with the credibility bank and the contrarian positions — every intersection is a new angle.

### Content Scaling Frameworks

**The Accordion Method** — Expand → Contract → Expand. This cycle never ends.

**70/20/10 Framework:** 70% proven content. 20% iterations. 10% big swings. The 10% is the most important and most neglected.

**Current phase:** Early data collection. Athens is the first real signal. Track what works, what energizes Evan, what the audience responds to.

### Trust Over Virality

Trust is the goal. The trust-building content pattern: identify the painful problem → share the unique solution → set clear expectations → make it actionable → repeat consistently.

### Cold Audience Principle

Every piece of content must work for someone who has zero clue who E.I. Werner is. No inside jokes, no unexplained references, no assumed knowledge of backstory. Critical during the launch phase.

---

## Platform Strategy

### Eye of Sauron — YouTube First

YouTube is the primary platform. It gets the pillar content: the long-form writing/gaming streams, the monthly update videos, the Outside Inn warmup/cooldown bookends. All energy, all innovation, all creative risk goes here first.

Twitch is secondary — simulcast from OBS, live community interaction, gaming culture home. No rebuild required. It receives the stream, not the innovation.

TikTok, Instagram, YouTube Shorts receive repurposed clips only. No original creation for these platforms in year one. One editor takes raw stream footage and outputs VODs plus clips — one person, one workflow, multiple outputs.

**This phase ends when YouTube feels dialed in.** Then the Eye rotates to short-form with real intention. Not before.

**The Outside Inn — Community Layer (updated Mar 5):** The Outside Inn architecture is now settled. It is not a second content brand — it is the community layer of the E.I. Werner world. The Outside Inn YouTube channel is part of that layer: a lower-stakes home for unscheduled streams, ambient broadcast, tech testing, and practice runs before major milestones. People who find it are self-selecting as the most invested audience. The channel is also the natural home for ambient radio when that gets turned on — Holdt animation, Carson's music, the inn as a place that exists even when Evan isn't actively streaming. Not formally launching yet. Evaluate in Athens. When it launches, it launches as the inside channel — not as a second brand.

**Wednesday Athens medium send:** The first outreach beyond the gaming community. Personal texts only — extended network, IRL friends, family. Not a social media blast. Not an email list push. Personal. This is intentional: the room needs soul before it needs scale.

