## Hardware & Streaming Infrastructure

*Full specs in OIS Hardware & Software Master (separate living document). This section covers principles relevant to brand decisions.*

### The Resilience Principle

The stream should not be fragile. If Evan has a laptop, a webcam, a mic, and a connection with 10+ Mbps upload on ethernet, he can stream reliably. No cancelled streams because the setup isn't perfect. No anxiety about streaming from a new location. The audience showed up for the writer, not the production value.

**Current deployment:** White Plains, NY → Athens, Greece ~March 11–May 15, 2026. Flatio booking (195/19 Mbps confirmed). Flights purchased. First month rent paid.

**OBS Scenes:**
- Outside Inn Warmup → Holdt animation + LofiLoop 100% + countdown + patron roll (Alagard font)
- Writing Stream → Facecam + Notion, music 20–30%, patron roll in Sprat (black and white)
- Gaming Stream → Facecam + game, music 20–30% or off
- Cooldown → Holdt animation + music 100%, patron roll (Alagard font)

All one-button via Stream Deck. No 24/7 radio. VPS stays available. The bookend is the atmosphere layer.

**Pre-stream checklist:** Built and saved as separate document. Not optional. Includes: YouTube "not made for kids" check, chat enabled check, Restream toggle check. These reset. The checklist is the insurance.

