## First Stream Learnings — March 3, 2026

### What Happened

Broadcast Alpha. First live stream since 2021. Zero sleep. 8 peak viewers. No overlay, no stream alerts, no polish. Just showed up.

### What Went Right

1. The tech worked. 11h39m Holdt radio without a drop. Live stream went out on YouTube and Twitch.
2. The 48-hour build sprint delivered. Animation loop, countdown timer, patron roll — all functional before stream.
3. He hit his stride a few times. Those moments are the proof of concept.
4. He kept collaborators informed.
5. Luiz signed his contract.
6. Carson got his contract + album offer.
7. Merch samples arrived.
8. He went for it.

### What Needs Work

1. The freeze. First time on camera since 2021, zero sleep. Only fix is reps.
2. Writing stream structure. Notion open with no framing felt like a classroom. Needs clear opening, visible session goal, audience engagement moments.
3. No overlay. Coming.
4. Merch quality issues. Desk mat too square, 10×10 print resolution too low.
5. Sleep. Can't do zero-sleep streams.

### Structural Decisions Made

- **Writing → Gaming per session** replaces the old 3 writing + 1 gaming weekly cadence.
- **70:07 warmup/cooldown** replaces the 24/7 radio concept. VPS stays available.
- **No 24/7 radio.** Deferred until headless OBS + deeper catalog justify it.

---

## Second Stream Learnings — March 4, 2026

### What Happened

Second stream. Still running on fumes post-launch. Showed up anyway. Encountered two new technical failures immediately on going live.

### What Went Wrong

1. **YouTube reset to "made for kids."** Chat locked. Waiting room viewers bounced when stream restarted to fix it. Lost real people who were waiting.
2. **Chat was disabled.** Same root cause — settings reset between streams without warning.

### What Was Learned

1. **YouTube settings reset between streams. Always.** This is not a one-time error. It will happen again if not checked. The pre-stream checklist now exists. This is the entire lesson.
2. **The checklist is not optional.** Even when you're tired, even when you think you already know, even when the last stream was fine. Check it every time.
3. **Waiting room viewers are real people.** Losing them to a restart is real. The checklist is cheap. Losing a waiting room is expensive.

### What Went Right

1. Adapted and restarted instead of abandoning the stream.
2. The checklist was built immediately after.
3. The freeze is smaller. The stride moments are longer. The reps are working.
4. Still showed up. Two streams in two days. That's the brand.

### Structural Decisions Made

- **Pre-stream checklist is now a permanent required document.** Not optional. Lives separately. Referenced before every stream.
- **Writing stream still needs more structure.** Writing without a clear goal and outline was tough. Come in with a defined session objective every time.

